            <biogHist>
                <p>Donald was the son of Neil MacPhee, sailor, and Marion MacPhee née MacLean. In
                    the 1841 census Donald is recorded as living with his widowed mother in Brèibhig
                    and, his age is stated as 25, with no sisters or brothers. Sometime before 1857
                    he married Mary née Haggart [Taggart], daughter of Peter and Rachel née
                    MacDougall, but she dies in childbirth in December 1857. In February 1859 he
                    married Ann Nicolson of Rhulios, daughter of Malcolm and Ann née McCruish and
                    settles in Brèibhig as a crofter. In 1861 the couple have a small family, two
                    sons: Donald (15) and Hector (10), and a daughter Rebecca (13). </p>
                <p>In December 1869, Donald MacPhee died from unknown causes, the witness on the
                    death certificate was his son Donald.</p>
                <p>Carmichael met Donald in March and May of 1867 where he recordeds several poems,
                    songs and stories.</p>
